modules.description: This module provides operations for creating, modifying, and slicing mutable byte sequences, with support for low-level memory manipulation, integer encoding/decoding, and substring searches. It works with bigstrings (`Bstr.t`), fixed-length, mutable sequences backed by Bigarray, enabling efficient byte-level access and in-place updates. Specific use cases include binary data processing, network protocol parsing, memory-mapped file handling, and scenarios requiring precise control over byte representations or high-performance data transformations.
